## 9. Best Practices Summary

### 9.1 Do's
- ✅ Provide clear, user-friendly error messages
- ✅ Implement proper error boundaries
- ✅ Use retry logic with exponential backoff
- ✅ Track errors for analytics and debugging
- ✅ Show loading states during async operations
- ✅ Handle network failures gracefully
- ✅ Validate user input before API calls
- ✅ Log errors for debugging

### 9.2 Don'ts
- ❌ Show technical error messages to users
- ❌ Ignore error tracking and logging
- ❌ Assume API calls will always succeed
- ❌ Use infinite retry loops
- ❌ Expose sensitive information in errors
- ❌ Block UI without loading indicators
- ❌ Skip input validation
- ❌ Forget to clean up resources on errors

